.SH NAME
ovs_vport_get_options \- retrieve device options
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ovs_vport_get_options
.BI "(const struct vport *vport "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vport" 12
vport from which to retrieve the options.
.IP "skb" 12
sk_buff where options should be appended.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Retrieves the configuration of the given device, appending an
OVS_VPORT_ATTR_OPTIONS attribute that in turn contains nested
vport-specific attributes to \fIskb\fP.

Returns 0 if successful, -EMSGSIZE if \fIskb\fP has insufficient room, or another
negative error code if a real error occurred.  If an error occurs, \fIskb\fP is
left unmodified.

Must be called with ovs_mutex or rcu_read_lock.
